{"title_page": "Matt Goss", "text_new": "{{short description|English singer-songwriter}}\n{{About|the singer|the cyclist|Matthew Goss}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Matt Goss\n| image           = MattGoss.jpg\n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Goss performing at the Bros reunion concert in 2017\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Matthew Weston Goss\n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1968|9|29|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Lewisham]], [[London]], [[England]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://search.findmypast.co.uk/results/world-records/england-and-wales-births-1837-2006?firstname=matthew+weston&lastname=goss&eventyear=1968&eventyear_offset=0|title=Search Results for England & Wales Births 1837-2006 - findmypast.co.uk|website=search.findmypast.co.uk}}</ref>\n| origin           = \n| death_date       = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date first) -->\n| death_place      = \n| genre            = \n| occupation       = Singer, songwriter\n| instrument       = \n| years_active     = 1986&ndash;present\n| label            = [[Decca Records|Decca]], [[Virgin Records|Virgin]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Bros (band)|Bros]], Co*Bra\n| website          = {{URL| http://www.mattgoss.biz}} \n| residence = [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], US\n| module           = \n| module2          = \n| module3          = \n}}\n\n'''Matthew Weston Goss''' (born 29 September 1968)<ref name=\"Riggs\">Riggs, Thomas (2003) ''Contemporary Theatre, Film and Television'', Gale, {{ISBN|978-0-7876-6363-6}}, p. 176</ref> is an English singer-songwriter and musician, currently based in [[Las Vegas, Nevada|Las Vegas]]. He is the lead singer of 1980s pop group [[Bros]], which also features his twin brother [[Luke Goss|Luke]] as drummer (and originally [[Craig Logan]] as bass player).\n\n==Bros==\n{{main|Bros}}\n\n==Solo career==\nMatt Goss began his solo career in 1995, and has enjoyed [[record chart|chart]] success with singles such as \"If You Were Here Tonight\" and \"I'm Coming With Ya\". He recorded the duet \"This Pain\" with his friend, [[Denise Pearson]] of [[Five Star]] in 1997, which was released on the Co*Bra album \"One\".<ref>{{cite web |title=CO*BRA - One (CD, Album) |url=https://www.discogs.com/COBRA-One/release/393344 |website=Discogs |accessdate=18 January 2019}}</ref> Goss worked with [[Paul Oakenfold]] on the single \"Firefly\", which was remixed and reached #1 on the World Trance chart.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wilson |first1=Mackenzie |title=Bros Crooner Matt Goss Returns to London |url=http://www.bbcamerica.com/anglophenia/2010/10/bros-crooner-matt-goss-returns-to-london |accessdate=18 January 2019 |publisher=BBC America}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2009, it was announced<ref>{{cite news |last1=Murphy |first1=Jay David |title=Singer Matt Goss debuting his show in Vegas |url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/article/279447 |accessdate=18 January 2019 |publisher=Digital Journal |date=19 September 2009}}</ref> that he would be playing live shows at the [[Palms Casino Resort]] in Las Vegas. By January 2010, the live show had moved to [[Caesars Palace]], playing at Cleopatra's Barge every Friday and Saturday night. In June 2010, he signed a three-year contract with Caesars Palace. His live show is produced by the creator of [[The Pussycat Dolls]], [[Robin Antin]]. The show played for one night at the [[Royal Albert Hall]], [[London]] on 19 October 2010 and returned on 21 October 2011. He has won several awards for his show<ref>{{cite news |title=Matt Goss has been given the keys to Las Vegas Strip |url=https://www.msn.com/en-sg/entertainment/celebrity/matt-goss-has-been-given-the-keys-to-las-vegas-strip/ar-BBLEUUk |accessdate=18 January 2019 |publisher=MSN |date=8 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Matt Goss scores key to Las Vegas honour |url=https://www.msn.com/en-gb/entertainment/celebrity/matt-goss-scores-key-to-las-vegas-honour/ar-BBLHlVO |accessdate=18 January 2019 |publisher=MSN |date=10 August 2018}}</ref>. In February 2011, Goss appeared in a [[Yorkshire Tea]] [[television advertisement]] campaign.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hyslop |first1=Leah |title=Yorkshire Tea looks to bring expat Brits a 'proper brew' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/expat/expatnews/8281196/Yorkshire-Tea-looks-to-bring-expat-Brits-a-proper-brew.html |accessdate=18 January 2019 |publisher=The Telegraph |date=25 January 2011}}</ref>\n\nMatt Goss signed a record deal with Decca Records for the UK release of his album ''[[Life_You_Imagine_(Matt_Goss_album)|Life You Imagine]]''. Goss worked on the album with music producer Ron Fair (Lady Gaga, U2, Black Eyed Peas, Christina Aguilera, Mary J. Blige) and enlisted the services of a 40-piece Hollywood orchestra. The album was released on 14 October 2013, with the collection including original material in addition to a big-band version of the Bros single \"[[When Will I Be Famous]]\".\n\nGoss's album ''Life You Imagine'' was released in the United States on 29 April 2014 by Virgin Records.\n\nGoss's single \"Gone Too Long\" was released internationally on 2 October 2016 to coincide with his return to Wembley Arena, London on 1 October.\n\n==Bibliography==\nMatt Goss authored two books: ''More Than You Know: The Autobiography'', published in 2005, and ''Bear Crimbo'', a children's story published in 2010.<ref name=\"Crimbo\">[http://www.bearcrimbo.com/ ''Crimbo the Bear'' site]. Retrieved on 18 March 2011</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n!colspan=\"1\"| Chart positions\n|-\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/14188/matt-goss/| title=Matt Goss - Album Chart Stats|publisher=Official Charts|accessdate=18 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''The Key''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Early_Side_of_Later_(album)|Early Side of Later]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 87\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Gossy]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Life_You_Imagine_(Matt_Goss_album)|Life You Imagine]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 27\n|}\n\n===Co*Bra studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n!colspan=\"1\"| Chart positions\n|-\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''One''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| -\n|-\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n!colspan=\"2\"| Chart positions\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<ref name=\"CS\">[https://www.officialcharts.com/artists/ Matt Goss], Chart Stats, retrieved 2010-05-15</ref><ref>[https://www.officialcharts.com/artists/ Minimal Chic Featuring Matt Goss], Chart Stats, retrieved 2010-05-15</ref>\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[Ultratop|BEL]]\n|-\n| 1995\n| \"[[The_Key_(Matt_Goss_song)|The Key]]\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 40\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 35\n|rowspan=\"3\"|''The Key''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 1996\n| \"Heaven is 10 Zillion Light Years Away\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| \"If You Were Here Tonight\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 23\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2003\n| \"I'm Coming With Ya\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 22\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"1\"| ''Non-album Single''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2004\n| \"Fly\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 31\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"1\"| ''Early Side of Later''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2006\n| \"It's the End of the Road\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"1\"| ''Non-album Single''\n|- \n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2009\n| \"Evil\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"2\"| ''Gossy''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2010\n| \"Firefly\" <small>(with [[Paul Oakenfold]])</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2011\n| \"Fighting For Love\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014 \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"1\"| ''Non-album Single''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2011\n| \"Strong\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014 \n|rowspan=\"3\"| ''Life You Imagine''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2014\n| \"I Do\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| \"Nothing Like This\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2016\n| \"A Vegas Summer\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"3\"| ''Non-album Single''\n|-\n| \"Gone Too Long\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2018\n| \"Red Flares\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|}\n\n===Co*Bra Singles===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n!colspan=\"1\"| Chart positions\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]\n|-\n| 1996\n| \"Vision\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"4\"|''One''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 1997\n| \"Living for the City\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| \"Love Sweet Love\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 1998\n| \"Free\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|}\n\n===As featured artist===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n!colspan=\"1\"| Chart positions\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]\n|-\n| 1995\n| \"Supermodel Sandwich W/Cheese\" <small>([[Terence Trent D'arby]] feat. Matt Goss)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"1\"|''[[Vibrator (album)|Vibrator]]''\n|-\n| 2004\n| \"I Need the Key\" <small>(Minimal Chic feat. Matt Goss)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 54\n|rowspan=\"3\"|''Non-album Single''\n|-\n| 2005\n| \"With Or Without You\" <small>(Minimal Chic feat. Matt Goss)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| 2013\n| \"Touch the Sky\" <small>([[Paul Oakenfold]], Matt Goss & The Concrete Sneakers)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* [http://mattgoss.la/2013/03/13/the-new-mg-album-is-finished/ Matt Goss New 2013 Album Is Called \"LIFE YOU IMAGINE\"]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110912140335/http://mattgoss.la/2011/05/25/new-matt-goss-album-to-be-produced-by-ron-fair/ Matt Goss New Album Produced By Ron Fair]\n* [http://mattgoss.la/2010/01/28/matt-goss-joins-caesars-place-for-new-vegas-show/ Matt Goss headliner at Caesars Palace]\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.mattgoss.biz}}\n* {{Official website|http://mattgoss.la|Matt Goss profile}} at MG Music\n* {{IMDb name|id=1519543|name=Matt Goss}}\n\n{{Bros}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Goss, Matt}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Bros members]]\n[[Category:Musicians from London]]\n[[Category:People from Lewisham]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:Identical twins]]\n[[Category:Twin people from England]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|English singer-songwriter}}\n{{About|the singer|the cyclist|Matthew Goss}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Matt Goss\n| image           = MattGoss.jpg\n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Goss performing at the Bros reunion concert in 2017\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Matthew Weston Goss\n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1968|9|29|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Lewisham]], [[London]], [[England]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://search.findmypast.co.uk/results/world-records/england-and-wales-births-1837-2006?firstname=matthew+weston&lastname=goss&eventyear=1968&eventyear_offset=0|title=Search Results for England & Wales Births 1837-2006 - findmypast.co.uk|website=search.findmypast.co.uk}}</ref>\n| origin           = \n| death_date       = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date first) -->\n| death_place      = \n| genre            = \n| occupation       = Singer, songwriter\n| instrument       = \n| years_active     = 1986&ndash;present\n| label            = [[Decca Records|Decca]], [[Virgin Records|Virgin]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Bros (band)|Bros]], Co*Bra\n| website          = {{URL| http://www.mattgoss.biz}} \n| residence = [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], US\n| module           = \n| module2          = \n| module3          = \n}}\n\n'''Matthew Weston Goss''' (born 29 September 1968)<ref name=\"Riggs\">Riggs, Thomas (2003) ''Contemporary Theatre, Film and Television'', Gale, {{ISBN|978-0-7876-6363-6}}, p. 176</ref> is an English singer-songwriter and musician, currently based in [[Las Vegas, Nevada|Las Vegas]]. He is the lead singer of 1980s pop group [[Bros]], which also features his twin brother [[Luke Goss|Luke]] as drummer (and originally [[Craig Logan]] as bass player).\n\n==Bros==\n{{main|Bros}}\n\n==Solo career==\nMatt Goss began his solo career in 1995, and has enjoyed [[record chart|chart]] success with singles such as \"If You Were Here Tonight\" and \"I'm Coming With Ya\". He recorded the duet \"This Pain\" with his friend, [[Denise Pearson]] of [[Five Star]] in 1997, which was released on the Co*Bra album \"One\"<ref>{{cite web |title=CO*BRA - One (CD, Album) |url=https://www.discogs.com/COBRA-One/release/393344 |website=Discogs |accessdate=18 January 2019}}</ref>. Goss worked with [[Paul Oakenfold]] on the single \"Firefly\", which was remixed and reached #1 on the World Trance chart<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wilson |first1=Mackenzie |title=Bros Crooner Matt Goss Returns to London |url=http://www.bbcamerica.com/anglophenia/2010/10/bros-crooner-matt-goss-returns-to-london |accessdate=18 January 2019 |publisher=BBC America}}</ref>.\n\nIn June 2009, it was announced<ref>{{cite news |last1=Murphy |first1=Jay David |title=Singer Matt Goss debuting his show in Vegas |url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/article/279447 |accessdate=18 January 2019 |publisher=Digital Journal |date=19 September 2009}}</ref> that he would be playing live shows at the [[Palms Casino Resort]] in Las Vegas. By January 2010, the live show had moved to [[Caesars Palace]], playing at Cleopatra's Barge every Friday and Saturday night. In June 2010, he signed a three-year contract with Caesars Palace. His live show is produced by the creator of [[The Pussycat Dolls]], [[Robin Antin]]. The show played for one night at the [[Royal Albert Hall]], [[London]] on 19 October 2010 and returned on 21 October 2011. He has won several awards for his show<ref>{{cite news |title=Matt Goss has been given the keys to Las Vegas Strip |url=https://www.msn.com/en-sg/entertainment/celebrity/matt-goss-has-been-given-the-keys-to-las-vegas-strip/ar-BBLEUUk |accessdate=18 January 2019 |publisher=MSN |date=8 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Matt Goss scores key to Las Vegas honour |url=https://www.msn.com/en-gb/entertainment/celebrity/matt-goss-scores-key-to-las-vegas-honour/ar-BBLHlVO |accessdate=18 January 2019 |publisher=MSN |date=10 August 2018}}</ref>. In February 2011, Goss appeared in a [[Yorkshire Tea]] [[television advertisement]] campaign.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hyslop |first1=Leah |title=Yorkshire Tea looks to bring expat Brits a 'proper brew' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/expat/expatnews/8281196/Yorkshire-Tea-looks-to-bring-expat-Brits-a-proper-brew.html |accessdate=18 January 2019 |publisher=The Telegraph |date=25 January 2011}}</ref>\n\nMatt Goss signed a record deal with Decca Records for the UK release of his album ''[[Life_You_Imagine_(Matt_Goss_album)|Life You Imagine]]''. Goss worked on the album with music producer Ron Fair (Lady Gaga, U2, Black Eyed Peas, Christina Aguilera, Mary J. Blige) and enlisted the services of a 40-piece Hollywood orchestra. The album was released on 14 October 2013, with the collection including original material in addition to a big-band version of the Bros single \"[[When Will I Be Famous]]\".\n\nGoss's album ''Life You Imagine'' was released in the United States on 29 April 2014 by Virgin Records.\n\nGoss's single \"Gone Too Long\" was released internationally on 2 October 2016 to coincide with his return to Wembley Arena, London on 1 October.\n\n==Bibliography==\nMatt Goss authored two books: ''More Than You Know: The Autobiography'', published in 2005, and ''Bear Crimbo'', a children's story published in 2010.<ref name=\"Crimbo\">[http://www.bearcrimbo.com/ ''Crimbo the Bear'' site]. Retrieved on 18 March 2011</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n!colspan=\"1\"| Chart positions\n|-\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/14188/matt-goss/| title=Matt Goss - Album Chart Stats|publisher=Official Charts|accessdate=18 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''The Key''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Early_Side_of_Later_(album)|Early Side of Later]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 87\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Gossy]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Life_You_Imagine_(Matt_Goss_album)|Life You Imagine]]''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 27\n|}\n\n===Co*Bra studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n!colspan=\"1\"| Chart positions\n|-\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''One''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| -\n|-\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n!colspan=\"2\"| Chart positions\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<ref name=\"CS\">[https://www.officialcharts.com/artists/ Matt Goss], Chart Stats, retrieved 2010-05-15</ref><ref>[https://www.officialcharts.com/artists/ Minimal Chic Featuring Matt Goss], Chart Stats, retrieved 2010-05-15</ref>\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[Ultratop|BEL]]\n|-\n| 1995\n| \"[[The_Key_(Matt_Goss_song)|The Key]]\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 40\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 35\n|rowspan=\"3\"|''The Key''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 1996\n| \"Heaven is 10 Zillion Light Years Away\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| \"If You Were Here Tonight\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 23\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2003\n| \"I'm Coming With Ya\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 22\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"1\"| ''Non-album Single''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2004\n| \"Fly\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 31\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"1\"| ''Early Side of Later''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2006\n| \"It's the End of the Road\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"1\"| ''Non-album Single''\n|- \n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2009\n| \"Evil\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"2\"| ''Gossy''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2010\n| \"Firefly\" <small>(with [[Paul Oakenfold]])</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2011\n| \"Fighting For Love\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014 \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"1\"| ''Non-album Single''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2011\n| \"Strong\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014 \n|rowspan=\"3\"| ''Life You Imagine''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2014\n| \"I Do\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| \"Nothing Like This\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2016\n| \"A Vegas Summer\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"3\"| ''Non-album Single''\n|-\n| \"Gone Too Long\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 2018\n| \"Red Flares\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|}\n\n===Co*Bra Singles===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n!colspan=\"1\"| Chart positions\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]\n|-\n| 1996\n| \"Vision\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"4\"|''One''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 1997\n| \"Living for the City\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| \"Love Sweet Love\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| 1998\n| \"Free\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n|}\n\n===As featured artist===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n!colspan=\"1\"| Chart positions\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n!style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]\n|-\n| 1995\n| \"Supermodel Sandwich W/Cheese\" <small>([[Terence Trent D'arby]] feat. Matt Goss)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|rowspan=\"1\"|''[[Vibrator (album)|Vibrator]]''\n|-\n|